The Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) has on Tuesday given approval to six companies to import milk and stopped every other importer in Nigeria of the product. The companies are FrieslandCampina; WAMCO Nigeria; Chi Limited; TG Arla Dairy Products Limited; Promasidor Nigeria Limited; Nestlé Nigeria PLC (MSK only) and Integrated Dairies Limited. In a circular number, TED/FEM/FPC/GEN/01/002 dated February 11, 2020 signed by the Director, Trade and Exchange Department CBN, Dr O.S NNAJI to all authorized dealers and the general public, the apex banking sector regulator said it has engaged with some companies in the industry. NLC calls for interrogation of ‘humongous’ N2trn… Gbajabiamila warns CBN, others against contempt of… Senate committee screens nominee for CBN deputy governor Senate screens Obiora for CBN deputy governor position ALSO READ: Senate adjourns over Longjan, to hold valedictory session for Uwajumogu These companies it stated, have keyed into the Bank’s backward integration program to enhance their capacity and improve local milk production. Accordingly, it wants all Authorised Dealers to note that all Forms ‘M’, for the importation of milk and its derivatives shall only be allowed for the six named companies. “For the avoidance of doubt, all established Forms ‘M’, for the importation of milk and its derivatives for companies other than the above for which shipment has not taken place should be cancelled immediately,” the circular read in part. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.